[
    {
        "content": "<p>a note about this:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/231634-beginners/topic/syntax.3A.20whitespace.20vs.20comma.20for.20items/near/402216037\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>actually <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/98df325d76b6b743c6b01f399bbbeaaf0d8108fa/www/wip_new_website/main.roc#L107\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/98df325d76b6b743c6b01f399bbbeaaf0d8108fa/www/wip_new_website/main.roc#L107</a> is a better example of the downside, would need to have parens across multiple lines if <code>homeLink</code> was moved ahead one spot:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nv\">nav</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">ariaLabel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"primary\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">div</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"top-bar-links\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/tutorial\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"tutorial\"</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/install\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"install\"</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/community\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"community\"</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/docs\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"docs\"</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/donate\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"donate\"</span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">]),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nv\">homeLink</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so in general DSLs that wanted to use function calls to make the elements would get a lot more parens!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>now that we have more whitespace sensitivity because of <code>!</code>, we have an option here that's at least worth discussing: we could make the following Just Work</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nv\">nav</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">ariaLabel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"primary\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nv\">div</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"top-bar-links\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/tutorial\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"tutorial\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/install\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"install\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/community\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"community\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/docs\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"docs\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">href</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/wip/donate\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">text</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"donate\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nv\">homeLink</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 442927839,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631388
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the way it would work is that if you go down a line without indenting, that's treated as a standalone list element</p>",
        "id": 442928022,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so basically instead of trailing commas, you have no commas at the end of lines in a list</p>",
        "id": 442928101,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631478
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(could work the same way for records)</p>",
        "id": 442928147,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631500
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>CoffeeScript had something like this as I recall</p>",
        "id": 442928157,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so this would mean we could do comma-separated function arguments, which has been a consistent recurring request from beginners that seems totally reasonable except for this DSL downside</p>",
        "id": 442928637,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717631698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>F# lists work like that also. Except it uses semicolons for the single line variant.</p>",
        "id": 442932873,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1717633667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Overall, I think I prefer the status quo, but I get the consistency argument</p>",
        "id": 442933389,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1717633913
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I can anticipate beginners being confused by this design too <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 442934442,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1717634395
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what if, the status quo stayed as the correct syntax, but in some cases when it's unambiguous, it still compiled with a warning, and the formatter fixed the commas. If it is ambiguous, it'd be a compile error. That could cut down on chasing syntax errors.</p>",
        "id": 443184512,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1717719475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is <code>[text \"...\"]</code> a sibling element to <code>a [...]</code> in the above example?</p>",
        "id": 443787888,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1718030853
    }
]